<subSubSection id="C3776556ED6F380BFF78FC13FE80FAAC" pageId="574" pageNumber="575" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED6F380BFF78FC13FE80FAAC" blockId="574.[136,778,173,1389]" pageId="574" pageNumber="575">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6F380BFF78FC13FEEFFC36" bold="true" box="[189,298,989,1015]" pageId="574" pageNumber="575">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFC4B2CED6F380BFEFBFC13FDE2FC36" author="Schellenberg, A." box="[318,551,989,1015]" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin" pageId="574" pageNumber="575" pagination="217 - 274" part="10" refId="ref330676" refString="Schellenberg, A. (1922) Neue Notodelphyiden des Berliner und Hamburger Museums mit einer Uberscht der ascidienwohnenden Gattungen und Arten. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 10 (2), 217 - 274. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnz. 4830100201" title="Neue Notodelphyiden des Berliner und Hamburger Museums mit einer Uberscht der ascidienwohnenden Gattungen und Arten" type="journal article" year="1922">Schellenberg (1922)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<typeStatus id="54D6887FED6F380BFD6EFC13FCCCFC39" box="[683,777,989,1016]" pageId="574" pageNumber="575">thetype</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED6F380BFF2EFBCEFE50FBD8" authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1922" box="[235,405,1023,1050]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Campopera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="574" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="michaelseni">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6F380BFF2EFBCEFF3BFBDB" box="[235,254,1024,1050]" italics="true" pageId="574" pageNumber="575">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6F380BFECAFC31FE50FBD8" box="[271,405,1023,1049]" italics="true" pageId="574" pageNumber="575">michaelseni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as an associate of the ascidian 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED6F380BFF4DFBEFFD56FBFA" authority="(Cunningham, 1871)" baseAuthorityName="Cunningham" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[136,659,1057,1083]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Molgulidae" genus="Paramolgula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pleurogona" pageId="574" pageNumber="575" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gigantea">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6F380BFF4DFBEFFE4AFBFA" box="[136,399,1057,1083]" italics="true" pageId="574" pageNumber="575">Paramolgula gigantea</emphasis>
(Cunningham, 1871)
</taxonomicName>
collected in the 
<collectingCountry id="F37A764DED6F380BFF1FFB8DFE58FB9C" box="[218,413,1091,1117]" name="Falkland Islands" pageId="574" pageNumber="575">Falkland Islands</collectingCountry>
. In the original description he provided figures of the habitus, rostrum, antennule, and leg 1. Two of the newspecies describedin the presentwork are immediately identifiable as belonging to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED6F380BFDBBFB64FCC7FB05" authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1922" box="[638,770,1194,1220]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Campopera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="574" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6F380BFDBBFB64FCC7FB05" box="[638,770,1194,1220]" italics="true" pageId="574" pageNumber="575">Campopera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, due to their characteristic caterpillar-like body form. The presence of a large claw on the basis of the maxilla, which Schellenberg (1992) mentioned as a diagnostic feature of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EED6F380BFF3AFAFCFE46FA8D" authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1922" box="[255,387,1330,1356]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Campopera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="574" pageNumber="575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED6F380BFF3AFAFCFE46FA8D" box="[255,387,1330,1356]" italics="true" pageId="574" pageNumber="575">Campopera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is confirmed in two new species describedbelow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
